%2Fi.insider.com%2F64af11e994be880019f3ad5f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221078%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bill%20Zhou%20%2F%20Photo%20by%20Heyang%20Qiu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20reason%20I%20could%20afford%20flying%20three%20times%20a%20week%20to%20school%20was%20that%20I%20had%20accumulated%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-are-points-miles-worth-value%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrequent-flier%20miles%20and%20credit-card%20points%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20Earlier%20in%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20took%20advantage%20of%20the%20cheap%20fares%20and%20flew%20a%20couple%20of%20%26quot%3Bmileage%20runs%26quot%3B%20(when%20you%20book%20the%20cheapest%20airfare%20for%20the%20furthest%20distance)%20to%20accumulate%20more%20miles%20and%20qualify%20for%20elite%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20had%20the%20highest%20elite%20status%20with%20Alaska%20Airlines%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20earn%202.5%20miles%20for%20every%20one%20I%20flew.%20By%20the%20time%20school%20started%20in%20August%2C%20I%20had%20850%2C000%20miles%20with%20Alaska%20Airlines%20and%20could%20use%20those%20miles%20to%20greatly%20reduce%20the%20cost%20of%20my%20commute.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20I%20knew%20what%20my%20class%20schedule%20looked%20like%2C%20I%20did%20a%20lot%20of%20planning%20and%20booked%20all%20my%20tickets%20in%20advance.%20Besides%20the%20month%20of%20August%2C%20all%20my%20travel%20dates%20fell%20within%20the%20off-peak%20travel%20season%2C%20so%20my%20tickets%20were%20much%20cheaper.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Alaska%20Airlines%2C%20I%20usually%20booked%20their%20mileage%20tickets%2C%20which%20start%20at%205%2C000%20miles%20one%20way%20and%20paid%20%245.60%20out%20of%20pocket%20to%20cover%20tax.%20This%20calculated%20to%20%241552.10%20and%20407%2C500%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Southwest%20flights%2C%20I%20booked%20most%20of%20the%20tickets%20during%20its%20Black%20Friday%2C%20Cyber%20Monday%2C%20and%20Valentine's%20Day%20sales%2C%20when%20flights%20were%20as%20cheap%20as%20%2430.%20This%20calculated%20to%20%24758.24%20and%20156%2C945%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20an%20additional%20%2471.30%20and%205%2C500%20miles%20on%20United%20flights%2C%20%2415.60%20and%206%2C500%20miles%20on%20Avianca%20flights%2C%20and%20%2415.90%20on%20Spirit%20flights.%20In%20total%2C%20I%20took%20238%20flights%20and%20spent%20%242%2C413.14%20on%20airfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20spent%2075%2C955%20minutes%20on%20my%20commute%2C%20equivalent%20to%20nearly%2053%20days%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bill%20Zhou%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64af106a94be880019f3acf5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBill%20Zhou%20plans%20out%20his%20commute%20schedule%20on%20the%20plane.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bill%20Zhou%20%2F%20Photo%20by%20Heyang%20Qiu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20scheduled%20all%20my%20classes%20to%20fall%20on%20Monday%2C%20Wednesday%2C%20and%20Friday.%20If%20I%20had%20to%20fly%20every%20day%20for%20the%20entire%20semester%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20have%20worked%20out.%20Door-to-door%2C%20the%20commute%20from%20my%20house%20to%20campus%20was%20around%204%20%C2%BD%20to%205%20hours%20each%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20beginning%20of%20the%20semester%20was%20pretty%20hectic%20because%20we%20had%20a%20two-week%20boot%20camp%20with%20engineering-leadership%20classes%20every%20day.%20Flying%20back%20and%20forth%20daily%20was%20exhausting%20%E2%80%94%20honestly%2C%20I%20barely%20made%20it%20through.%20I%20thought%20about%20giving%20up%20at%20one%20point%2C%20but%20it%20was%20too%20late%20to%20find%20an%20apartment.%20And%20I%20already%20had%20all%20my%20tickets%20booked.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20fall%20semester%2C%20I%20would%20wake%20up%20at%203%3A40%20a.m.%20and%20leave%20home%20by%204%3A20%20a.m.%20Then%20I%20would%20drive%2030%20minutes%20to%20the%20metro%20station%20by%20Los%20Angeles%20International%20Airport%20and%20park%20there.%20Parking%20at%20the%20station%20was%20%243%20a%20day%2C%20compared%20with%20%2450%20a%20day%20at%20the%20main%20terminal.%20About%204%3A50%20a.m.%2C%20I%20would%20take%20the%20shuttle%20to%20LAX.%20The%20shuttle%20arrives%20every%2010%20minutes%20and%20takes%20between%2010%20to%2015%20minutes%20depending%20on%20which%20terminal%20you're%20going%20to.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20reach%20the%20airport%20about%205%3A10%20a.m.%2C%2010%20minutes%20before%20boarding%20began.%20The%20TSA%20security%20check%20wasn't%20really%20an%20issue%20this%20early%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20would%20typically%20take%20me%20only%2010%20minutes%20to%20get%20through.%20My%20flight%20would%20take%20off%20from%20LAX%20at%206%3A00%20a.m.%20and%20land%20in%20San%20Francisco%20no%20later%20than%207%3A30%20a.m.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221438%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bill%20Zhou%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64af13e394be880019f3adf0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221078%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bill%20Zhou%20%2F%20Photo%20by%20Heyang%20Qiu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20landing%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20I%20would%20go%20to%20the%20Alaska%20Airlines%20lounge%20from%207%3A30%20a.m.%20to%208%3A30%20a.m.%20and%20eat%20breakfast%2C%20catch%20up%20on%20homework%2C%20and%20reply%20to%20emails.%20Then%20I%20would%20take%20the%20BART%20train%20from%20the%20airport%20to%20downtown%20Berkeley%2C%20which%20took%20around%20an%20hour.%20About%209%3A45%20a.m.%2C%20I%20would%20take%20either%20the%20AC%20Transit%2052%20bus%2C%20the%20F%20line%2C%20or%20the%20UC%20Berkeley%20campus%20shuttle%20to%20go%20up%20the%20hill%20to%20my%20first%20class%20at%2010%3A10%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20classes%20ended%20around%202%20p.m.%2C%20but%20I%20usually%20stayed%20later%20to%20meet%20with%20classmates%2C%20work%20on%20projects%2C%20and%20finish%20my%20homework.%20I%20would%20typically%20leave%20campus%20around%205%20p.m.%2C%20take%20the%20BART%20to%20San%20Francisco%20International%20Airport%20and%20arrive%20at%20the%20airport%20around%206%3A15%20p.m.%2C%20in%20time%20to%20catch%20the%207%20p.m.%20Alaska%20Airlines%20flight.%20I%20would%20get%20into%20LAX%20around%208%3A30%20p.m.%2C%20take%20the%20shuttle%20to%20get%20to%20my%20car%20by%209%20p.m.%2C%20and%20then%20drive%20the%2030%20minutes%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20spring%20semester%2C%20I%20did%20a%20similar%20commute%2C%20except%20my%20first%20class%20didn't%20start%20until%20noon.%20So%20I%20would%20usually%20take%20an%208%3A20%20a.m.%20Southwest%20flight%20to%20the%20Oakland%20airport.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20never%20missed%20a%20class%20and%20graduated%20with%20a%203.88%20GPA%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221438%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bill%20Zhou%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64af133f8ed31300199eb4e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221078%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bill%20Zhou%20%2F%20Photo%20by%20Heyang%20Qiu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20almost%20never%20dealt%20with%20flight%20delays%20on%20the%20way%20to%20school%20because%20my%20flights%20were%20usually%20the%20first%20ones%20out%20in%20the%20morning.%20Later%20in%20the%20afternoon%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairline-flight-delays-higher-after-3-pm-report-2022-10%5C%22%3Eflights%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20delayed%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20first%20flight%20is%20almost%20always%20on%20time.%20Sometimes%2C%20it%20would%20get%20stressful%20traveling%20to%20the%20airport%20in%20the%20morning%20if%20there%20was%20an%20accident%20on%20the%20freeway%20or%20the%20BART%20was%20delayed.%20%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazingly%2C%20I%20never%20missed%20a%20class.%20I%20graduated%20with%20a%203.88%20GPA.%20Including%20airfare%2C%20gas%2C%20parking%2C%20and%20a%20%24491%20ticket%20I%20got%20from%20the%20California%20Highway%20Patrol%2C%20the%20commute%20cost%20me%20approximately%20%246%2C100%20for%20the%20year.%20In%20total%2C%20I%20spent%2075%2C955%20minutes%20on%20my%20commute%2C%20equivalent%20to%2052.75%2024-hour%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20passion%20for%20aviation%20and%20public%20transit%20made%20the%20commute%20more%20enjoyable%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bill%20Zhou%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64af114c8ed31300199eb466%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Bill%20Zhou%20%2F%20Photo%20by%20Heyang%20Qiu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20recommend%20anyone%20try%20this%20unless%20they're%20interested%20in%20transportation%20like%20I%20am.%20For%20me%2C%20I%20didn't%20view%20this%20as%20a%20dreadful%20commute%20%E2%80%94%20but%20as%20a%20small%20trick%20every%20time%20I%20got%20to%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20pretty%20happy%20flying%20and%20taking%20public%20transportation%20and%20enjoy%20the%20process%2C%20but%20not%20everybody%20would%20feel%20the%20same.%20Also%2C%20it%20was%20affordable%20only%20because%20I%20had%20so%20many%20flight%20miles.%20If%20I%20had%20to%20pay%20for%20every%20ticket%20in%20cash%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20have%20worked%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20this%20experience%20was%20worth%20it.%20This%20is%20probably%20one%20of%20the%20wildest%20things%20I've%20done%2C%20and%20I'm%20so%20glad%20I%20made%20it%20through%20without%20missing%20any%20classes.%20That%20itself%20is%20a%20miracle.%20Also%2C%20it's%20a%20great%20way%20for%20me%20to%20demonstrate%20my%20dedication%20and%20commitment%20to%20achieving%20a%20specific%20goal%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20all%20that%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-to-berkeley-super-commute-plane-student-high-rent-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689265933000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b0261a9751e3001929f9ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-to-berkeley-super-commute-plane-student-high-rent-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bill%20Zhou%20spent%2075%2C955%20minutes%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%2053%20days%20%E2%80%94%20flying%20from%20LA%20to%20the%20Bay%20Area%20three%20times%20a%20week%20while%20completing%20a%20one-year%20master's%20degree.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22htowey%40insider.com%20(Hannah%20Towey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-to-berkeley-super-commute-plane-student-high-rent-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Woman%20Who%20Interviewed%20Dawood%20Ibrahim.%20Not%20Just%20Once%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EShe%20says%20she%20first%20met%20fugitive%20don%20Dawood%20Ibrahim%20when%20he%20was%20a%20small-time%20criminal%20and%20was%20%26quot%3Bjust%20emerging%26quot%3B.%20She%20met%20him%20multiple%20times%20over%20the%20years%20and%20also%20interviewed%20him%2C%20both%20in%20India%20and%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20is%20seasoned%20journalist%20Sheela%20Bhatt%2C%20who%20sent%20the%20interwebs%20buzzing%20when%20she%20posted%20a%20throwback%20picture%20last%20month%20featuring%20her%20and%20Dawood%20Ibrahim%2C%20India's%20most%20wanted.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20picture%20was%20taken%20in%201988%20when%20Ms%20Bhatt%2C%20a%20journalist%20spanning%20four%20decades%2C%20visited%20Dubai%20to%20interview%20the%20don%2C%20who%20is%20wanted%20for%20multiple%20terror%20activities%20in%20India%2C%20including%20the%201993%20Mumbai%20serial%20blasts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Ms%20Bhatt's%20picture%20in%20Chitralekha%20magazine%20with%20Karim%20Lala%2C%20a%20mafia%20don%20of%20Mumbai%20in%20the%20late%201970s%2C%20which%20got%20her%20Dawood's%20attention.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDawood%20called%20her%20to%20help%20write%20against%20the%20alleged%20harassment%20of%20the%20girls%20in%20a%20government%20remand%20home%20on%20Mohammad%20Ali%20Road%20in%20Mumbai%20by%20the%20men%20of%20Karim%20Lala%2C%20she%20said%20in%20the%20interview.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EAap%20Karim%20Lala%20ko%20mil%20leto%20ho.%20Kaise%20hamari%20bachiyon%20ko%20pareshan%20karte%20hain%2C%20aap%20ispe%20likhye%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%20You%20met%20Karim%20Lala.%20You%20please%20write%20about%20how%20his%20men%20are%20harassing%20the%20girls)%2C%26quot%3B%20Dawood%20said%20over%20the%20phone%2C%20she%20told%20her%20interviewer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDawood%20was%20just%20an%20emerging%20man%20and%20his%20bosses%20were%20Marwari%2C%20Sindhi%2C%20Punjabi%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20in%201981-82%20he%20was%20just%20a%20criminal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20that%20telephone%20call%2C%20the%20first%20interview%20happened.%20She%20went%20with%20her%20husband%20to%20meet%20the%20don.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFirst%2C%20they%20called%20us%20at%20Tanker%20street%20near%20jail%20road%20(Mumbai).%20Then%20they%20got%20us%20in%20a%20car%20with%20tinted%20windows%20and%20took%20us%20to%20Pakmodia%20street%2C%20which%20I%20knew%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%20we%20met.%20Me%2C%20my%20husband%2C%20Dawood%20and%20Chhota%20Shakeel%20(Dawood's%20aide)%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20was%20doing%20the%20small%20talk.%20The%20only%20thing%20he%20wanted%20to%20say%20was%20that%20Karim%20Lala%20is%20a%20bad%20man%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20after%20that%20meeting%2C%20Ms%20Bhatt%20said%20she%20again%20met%20the%20don%20in%20a%20Baroda%20jail.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Ms%20Bhatt%20was%20living%20in%20Bombay%20(now%20Mumbai)%20and%20would%20visit%20Gujarat%20to%20report.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20managed%20to%20gain%20access%20and%20visited%20Baroda%20jail.%20To%20her%20surprise%2C%20she%20found%20Dawood%20playing%20football%20in%20there.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDawood%20said%20he%20won't%20spare%20Alamzeb%20(%20who%20used%20to%20run%20Karim%20Lala's%20businesses%20in%20Mumbai)%20and%20I%20wrote%20about%20it.%20It%20came%20true%20as%20Alamzeb%20died%20sometime%20after%20the%20article%20was%20published%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20contact%20for%20the%20next%202-3%20years%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FEV12kN4L_MA%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22EP-79%20%7C%20Mumbai's%20Underworld%2C%20Interviewing%20Dawood%20to%20Delhi's%20politics%20and%20much%20more%20with%20Sheela%20Bhatt%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201987%2C%20Dawood%20called%20again.%20This%20time%20from%20Dubai%2C%20according%20to%20her.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20several%20calls%2C%20she%20got%20an%20appointment%20and%20flew%20to%20Dubai%20in%201988%20to%20interview%20him%20about%20the%20drug%20business%20but%20her%20real%20worry%20wasn't%20meeting%20Dawood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20more%20worried%20about%20the%20money%20spent%20on%20ticket%20(Rs%203%2C500)%20than%20meeting%20Dawood%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20she%20%26quot%3Bhad%20no%20fear%26quot%3B%20and%20had%20previously%20interviewed%20or%20met%20Jarnail%20Singh%20Bhindranwale%2C%20Chhota%20Rajan%2C%20Yusuf%20Patel%2C%20Haji%20Mastan%2C%20Arun%20Gawli%20-%20all%20dreaded%20names%20in%20the%20underworld.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20she%20was%20sent%20by%20someone%20to%20interview%20Dawood%2C%20she%20shot%20back%3A%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EMain%20No%201%20ki%20reporter%20hoon%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%20I%20am%20the%20No%201%20reporter).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0On%20the%20first%20day%20in%20Dubai%2C%20Dawood%20said%20no%20to%20the%20interview%20and%20said%20%26quot%3Blet's%20eat%26quot%3B.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20came%20back%20the%20next%20day%20and%20he%20still%20denied%20her%20the%20interview%2C%20but%20chatted%20a%20lot.%20At%20one%20point%20even%20tried%20on%20Italian%20suits%2C%20asking%20for%20her%20impressions.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EModelling%20kar%20raha%20tha%3C%2Fem%3E%20(He%20was%20modelling)%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20interview%20happened%20on%20the%20third%20day%20but%20she%20was%20not%20allowed%20to%20tape%20it.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20saw%20my%20diary%20and%20took%20it.%20Then%20talked%20about%20the%20three%20murders%20in%20which%20he%20was%20involved%20including%20Alamzeb's.%20He%20said%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EAgar%20main%20usey%20nahi%20marta%20toh%20who%20mujhe%20maar%20deta.%20Bolo%20Sheela%20ji%20mujhe%20usey%20nahi%20maarna%20chahiye%20tha%3C%2Fem%3E%20(If%20I%20had%20not%20killed%20him%2C%20he%20would%20have%20killed%20me.%20You%20tell%20me%2C%20Sheela%20ji%2C%20should%20I%20not%20have%20killed%20him)%26quot%3B.%20I%20did%20not%20say%20anything.%2C%20I%20was%20just%20reporting%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22e7lii9cg%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fe7lii9cg_diary-1200_625x300_13_July_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESheela%20Bhatt's%20diary%20where%20she%20recorded%20all%20the%20phone%20numbers%2C%20gangsters%20included.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20had%20the%20trust%20that%20I%20will%20write%20the%20things%20as%20they%20are%20and%20not%20twist%20his%20words%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20her%20interviewer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20her%20last%20conversation%2C%20she%20said%20it%20was%20in%202002%20when%20Pervez%20Musharraf%20was%20visiting%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20conversation%2C%20she%20gave%20him%20the%20example%20of%20Phoolan%20Devi.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689265920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F9u640h28_sheela-dawood-1200_625x300_13_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsheela-bhatt-the-woman-who-interviewed-dawood-ibrahim-and-not-just-once-4204811%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22She%20says%20she%20first%20met%20fugitive%20don%20Dawood%20Ibrahim%20when%20he%20was%20a%20small-time%20criminal%20and%20was%20%26quot%3Bjust%20emerging%26quot%3B.%20She%20met%20him%20multiple%20times%20over%20the%20years%20and%20also%20interviewed%20him%2C%20both%20in%20India%20and%20Dubai.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsheela-bhatt-the-woman-who-interviewed-dawood-ibrahim-and-not-just-once-4204811%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsheela-bhatt-the-woman-who-interviewed-dawood-ibrahim-and-not-just-once-4204811%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsheela-bhatt-the-woman-who-interviewed-dawood-ibrahim-and-not-just-once-4204811%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20celebs%20revealed%20their%20fav%20sex%20positions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689265551000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101735596%2Cimgsize-59144.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofind