2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-1%2C%20India's%20maiden%20mission%20to%20the%20Moon%2C%20launched%20in%20October%202008%20and%20remained%20operational%20till%20August%202009.%20It%20changed%20humanity's%20understanding%20of%20the%20celestial%20body%20by%20confirming%20the%20presence%20of%20water%20molecules%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20using%20its%20Moon%20Impact%20Probe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20mission%2C%20Chandrayaan-2%2C%20launched%20in%20July%202019%20and%20reached%20the%20Moon's%20orbit%20in%20August.%20The%20lander%20deviated%20from%20the%20planned%20trajectory%20while%20attempting%20to%20land%20on%20September%206%20and%20suffered%20a%20hand%20landing.%20The%20orbiter%2C%20however%2C%20continues%20to%20function%20around%20the%20Moon%20in%20a%20very%20healthy%20state%20and%20has%20provided%20a%20lot%20of%20data%20to%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20help%20with%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaking%20Flight%20Again%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EISRO%20Chief%20S%20Somnath%20is%20confident%20that%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%2C%20which%20is%20scheduled%20to%20lift%20off%20from%20Sriharikota%20at%202.35%20pm%20tomorrow%2C%20could%20catapult%20India%20into%20the%20select%20list%20of%20nations%20that%20have%20achieved%20a%20controlled%20landing%20on%20the%20Moon.%20Currently%2C%20there%20are%20only%20three%20countries%20on%20that%20list%20-%20Russia%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mission%20has%20three%20primary%20objectives%3A%20To%20demonstrate%20a%20safe%20and%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%3B%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20rover's%20roving%20capabilities%20on%20the%20Moon%3B%20and%20to%20conduct%20scientific%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rocket%20being%20used%20is%20the%20Launch%20Vehicle%20Mark%20III%20(LVM-III)%2C%20which%20was%20earlier%20called%20the%20Geosynchronous%20Satellite%20Launch%20Vehicle%20Mark%20III.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20propulsion%20module%20will%20take%20the%20orbiter%2C%20the%20Vikram%20lander%20and%20the%20Pragyan%20rover%20to%20the%20lunar%20orbit.%20The%20lander%20will%20then%20softly%20touch%20down%20near%20the%20Moon's%20South%20Pole%20around%20August%2023%20and%20deploy%20the%20rover.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELessons%20Learnt%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20scientific%20experiments%20both%20on%20the%20lander%20and%20the%20rover%20and%20ISRO%20hopes%20to%20be%20able%20to%20carry%20out%20all%20of%20them%2C%20but%20the%20critical%20thing%20is%20to%20have%20a%20soft%20landing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20changes%20have%20been%20made%20to%20the%20lander%2C%20with%20one%20of%20the%20big%20ones%20being%20that%20the%20legs%20have%20been%20made%20more%20robust.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Chandrayaan-2%20had%20five%20engines%20on%20the%20Vikram%20lander%2C%20leading%20to%20anomalies%2C%20the%20lander%20on%20Chandrayaan-3%20will%20have%20only%20four%20engines%2C%20which%20could%20give%20it%20more%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20software%20has%20been%20improved%20and%20rigorous%20testing%20of%20both%20the%20hardware%20and%20the%20software%20has%20been%20done.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Somanath%20said%20that%20the%20new%20mission%20has%20been%20designed%20to%20land%20successfully%20even%20if%20certain%20elements%20fail.%20Several%20scenarios%2C%20including%20sensor%20failure%2C%20engine%20failure%2C%20algorithm%20failure%2C%20and%20calculation%20failure%20were%20examined%20and%20measures%20developed%20to%20counteract%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20essential%20lesson%20is%2C%20in%20any%20space%20mission%20the%20focus%20should%20be%20on%20conditions%20of%20normality.%20So%2C%20how%20we%20address%20them%20and%20how%20we%20mitigate%20the%20possibilities%20of%20a%20failure%20in%20such%20an%20event%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Somanath%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EISRO%20hopes%20to%20land%20Vikram%20at%20the%20same%20spot%20where%20the%20lander%20of%20Chandrayaan-2%20-%20which%20also%20bore%20the%20same%20name%20-%20had%20attempted%20to%20touch%20down.%20The%20landing%20spot%20will%20be%20close%20to%20the%20South%20Pole%20of%20the%20Moon%2C%20%C2%A0essentially%20because%20of%20the%20presence%20of%20water%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGathering%20Data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lander%20and%20rover%20are%20expected%20to%20have%20a%20life%20of%20one%20lunar%20day%20-%20equivalent%20to%2014%20Earth%20days%20-%20and%20will%20carry%20the%20same%20instruments%20as%20their%20predecessors%20on%20Chandrayaan-2.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20lander%20and%20rover%20will%20study%20the%20surface%20and%20atmosphere%20of%20the%20Moon%2C%20the%20orbiter%20will%20turn%20its%20focus%20to%20Earth%20to%20look%20at%20signatures%20of%20life%20on%20the%20Pale%20Blue%20Dot%20so%20that%20it%20can%20aid%20in%20the%20search%20of%20exoplanets%20(planets%20beyond%20the%20solar%20system)%20that%20may%20support%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lander%20and%20rover%20will%20study%20the%20low-height%20atmospheric%20characteristics%20and%20electrostatic%20characteristics%20of%20the%20Moon.%20ISRO%20also%20hopes%20to%20be%20able%20to%20pierce%20a%20sensor%20into%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20Moon%20to%20a%20depth%20of%20about%2010%20cm%20and%20measure%20the%20thermophysical%20characteristics%20of%20the%20lunar%20regolith%20(the%20layer%20of%20unconsolidated%20solid%20material%20covering%20the%20bedrock).%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689262920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Ffokoso4k_chandrayaan_625x300_13_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-how-indias-third-shot-at-the-moon-will-be-different-4204807%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20the%20rocket%20carrying%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20lifts%20off%20from%20Sriharikota%20tomorrow%20afternoon%2C%20India%20will%20look%20to%20build%20on%20the%20spectacular%20success%20of%20the%20first%20mission%20and%20hope%20to%20avoid%20the%20mistakes%20of%20the%20second.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-how-indias-third-shot-at-the-moon-will-be-different-4204807%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-how-indias-third-shot-at-the-moon-will-be-different-4204807%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-how-indias-third-shot-at-the-moon-will-be-different-4204807%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22If%20you%20left%20your%20cocaine%20at%20the%20White%20House%2C%20you're%20in%20the%20clear%20now%3A%20reports%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224985%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20White%20House%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b018e59751e3001929f5e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223738%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20White%20House%20is%20seen%2C%20July%2030%2C%202022%2C%20in%20Washington.%3Cp%3EManuel%20Balce%20Ceneta%2FAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Secret%20Service%20concluded%20their%20investigation%20into%20the%20cocaine%20bag%20without%20identifying%20any%20suspects.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20AP%20reports%20no%20DNA%20or%20fingerprints%20were%20found%20on%20the%20bag.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESurveillance%20footage%20of%20the%20area%20in%20the%20West%20Wing%20also%20was%20no%20help%20in%20finding%20the%20culprit.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECongratulations%20are%20in%20order%20for%20whoever%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-cocaine-guest-entrance-washington-post-2023-7%5C%22%3Eleft%20their%20bag%20of%20cocaine%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20White%20House%20earlier%20this%20month.%20The%20Secret%20Service%20has%20concluded%20their%20investigation%20into%20the%20incident%20without%20identifying%20any%20suspects%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F07%2F13%2Fpolitics%2Fwhite-house-cocaine-investigation%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.ap.org%2Fdetail%2FNofingerprintsDNAsampleorleadsfromcocainefoundattheWhiteHousetheSecretServicesays%2Fe6bf17a4bfe7d450aa66005ad6feeec6%2Ftext%3FhpSectionId%3D8b012cffa0df4fdfb4bb50e8a8d38d54%26st%3Dhpsection%26mediaType%3Dtext%2Cphoto%2Cvideo%2Cgraphic%2Caudio%26dateRange%3DAnytime%26totalCount%3D39%26currentItemNo%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20the%20first%20to%20report.%20And%20even%20more%20impressively%20for%20the%20culprit%3A%20No%20DNA%20or%20fingerprints%20were%20found%20on%20the%20coke-filled%20baggie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20physical%20evidence%2C%20the%20investigation%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20single%20out%20a%20person%20of%20interest%20from%20the%20hundreds%20of%20individuals%20who%20passed%20through%20the%20vestibule%20where%20the%20cocaine%20was%20discovered%2C%26quot%3B%20Secret%20Service%20officials%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkyledcheney%2Fstatus%2F1679509266300825601%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20summary%20of%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cocaine%20was%20discovered%20July%202%20in%20the%20West%20Wing%20inside%20one%20of%20the%20cubbies%20where%20people%20leave%20their%20phones%20behind%20for%20tours%2C%20leading%20law%20enforcement%20agents%20to%20believe%20the%20perpetrator%20was%20likely%20a%20tourist.%20The%20discovery%20prompted%20a%20brief%20evacuation%20of%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cocaine%20was%20confirmed%20as%20cocaine%20by%20subsequent%20lab