ause%20it'll%20help%20get%20Disney's%20streaming%20business%20profitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20subscription%20growth%20softening%2C%20though%2C%20he%20also%20acknowledged%20that%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20to%20do.%20Iger%20defended%20Disney%2B's%20low%20price%20at%20launch%2C%20saying%20the%20goal%20at%20the%20time%20was%20to%20put%20price%20pressure%20on%20competitors%20and%20meet%20Wall%20Street's%20demand%20for%20growth.%20He's%20since%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-plus-price-hikes-likely-to-ad-free-tier-others-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20prices%20were%20coming%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20streamer%20Disney%2B%20and%20that%20the%20company%20would%20be%20more%20selective%20about%20spending%20on%20content%20and%20what%20gets%20marketed.%20He%20also%20said%20he%20wouldn't%20rule%20out%20doing%20some%20licensing%2C%20a%20reversal%20of%20media%20companies'%20recent%20practice%20of%20keeping%20all%20their%20content%20on%20their%20own%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20recent%20box%20office%20misses%20in%20Pixar's%20%26quot%3BElemental%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Little%20Mermaid%2C%26quot%3B%20Iger%20acknowledged%20Disney's%20zeal%20to%20grow%20its%20streaming%20business%20contributed%20to%20some%20%26quot%3Bdisappointments.%26quot%3B%20Disney%20may%20have%20trained%20people%20to%20skip%20the%20theater%20by%20sending%20new%20releases%20directly%20to%20streaming%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20He%20also%20said%20by%20supercharging%20Marvel's%20output%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20ended%20up%20taxing%20people%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20time%20and%20focus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-hollywood-actors-writers-strike-could-end-nightmare-scenario%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWGA%20and%20imminent%20SAG-AFTRA%20s