C%20which%20had%20skipped%20the%20Patna%20meet%20has%20confirmed%20its%20participation%20for%20the%20Bengaluru%20one.%20The%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20which%20had%20attended%20the%20Patna%20meet%20but%20had%20skipped%20the%20press%20conference%20will%20attend%20the%20Bengaluru%20meeting%20as%20well%2C%20according%20to%20leaders%20of%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20in%20Patna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Congress%20has%20not%20yet%20assured%20the%20AAP%20of%20its%20support%20on%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20government%E2%80%99s%20ordinance%20nullifying%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20to%20give%20the%20Delhi%20government%20larger%20control%20over%20the%20bureaucracy%20in%20the%20state%2C%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20%E2%80%9Calmost%20convinced%E2%80%9D%20his%20Delhi%20counterpart%20Arvind%20Kejriwal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStrategists%20working%20with%20Nitish%20Kumar%20said%20that%20the%20Bengaluru%20meet%20might%20see%20the%20formation%20of%20three%20working%20groups%20which%20will%20draft%20a%20common%20agenda%20for%20opposition%20parties%20with%20the%20polls%20in%20mind.%20The%20meet%20is%20also%20likely%20to%20decide%20upon%20a%20common%20name%20for%20the%20opposition%20alliance.%20The%20parties%20are%20also%20likely%20to%20discuss%20tricky%20seat%20sharing%20arrangements%20among%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20parties%20which%20are%20likely%20to%20attend%20the%20meet%20are%20the%20Revolutionary%20Socialist%20Party%2C%20Indian%20Union%20Muslim%20League%2C%20Kerala%20Congress%20(M)%2C%20Viduthalai%20Chiruthaigal%20Katchi%2C%20Marumalarchi%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%2C%20Kerala%20Congress%20(J)%20and%20Forward%20Bloc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20parties%20which%20are%20scheduled%20to%20attend%20the%20July%2017-18%20meet%20share%20150%20MPs%20among%20themselves%20in%20the%20current%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Congress%20president%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20is%20likely%20to%20host%20a%20dinner%20for%20opposition%20party%20leaders%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20meet%20on%20July%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20will%20crystallise%20how%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%20the%20largest%20national%20party%20in%20the%20opposition%20%E2%80%93%20sees%20its%20own%20role%20in%20solidifying%20the%20anti-BJP%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Fpolitics%2Fpatna-amidst-aap-congress-sparring-16-opposition-parties-vow-to-unitedly-fight-the-bjp%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3E16%20Parties%20Vow%20to%20Unitedly%20Fight%20the%20BJP%2C%20Hark%20Back%20to%20Patna%E2%80%99s%20Historic%20Role%20in%20Opposition%20Unity%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETop%20four%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20exercise%20to%20unite%20opposition%20parties%2C%20which%20began%20about%2011%20months%20ago%2C%20has%20witnessed%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20the%20stature%20of%20four%20leaders%20%E2%80%93%20Nitish%20Kumar%2C%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%2C%20party%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20boss%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%E2%80%99s%20role%20assumes%20importance%20considering%20the%20open%20secret%20that%20his%20Bengal%20counterpart%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20is%20not%20ready%20to%20work%20with%20the%20Congress%20and%20that%20Samajwadi%20Party%20leader%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20too%20is%20uncomfortable%20with%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20Nitish%20has%20made%20efforts%20to%20get%20these%20two%20parties%20with%20conflicting%20interests%20in%20respective%20states%20to%20join%20the%20common%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMallikarjun%20Kharge%20has%20outdone%20his%20own%20reputation%20in%20displaying%20extraordinary%20political%20acumen%20in%20dealing%20with%20tricky%20situations%20within%20his%20own%20party%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmallikarjun-kharge-shows-his-mettle-and-guile-in-parliament%5C%22%3EMallikarjun%20Kharge%20Shows%20His%20Mettle%20and%20Guile%20in%20Parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20brought%20victory%20for%20his%20party%20in%20Karnataka%20and%20then%20sorted%20out%20the%20differences%20between%20the%20Karnataka%20CM%20Siddaramaiah%20and%20his%20deputy%20D.K.%20Shivakumar.%20He%20has%2C%20ostensibly%2C%20worked%20to%20maintain%20a%20delicate%20balance%20between%20the%20Rajasthan%20CM%20Ashok%20Gehlot%20and%20his%20rival%20Sachin%20Pilot%2C%20and%20done%20the%20same%20between%20Chhattisgarh%20CM%20Bhupesh%20Baghel%20and%20his%20rival%20turned%20deputy%20T.%20S.%20Singh%20Deo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20losing%20his%20MP%20role%20following%20his%20conviction%20in%20a%20defamation%20case%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20continuous%20machinations%20against%20him%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20has%20has%20made%20efforts%20in%20connecting%20with%20the%20masses%2C%20particularly%20agriculturists.%20Rahul%E2%80%99s%20popularity%20draws%20comparisons%20with%20his%20grandmother%20Indira%20Gandhi%20and%20photographs%20showing%20him%20with%20the%20farm%20workers%20in%20muddy%20fields%20must%20add%20to%20the%20discomfiture%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%20who%20often%20draws%20flak%20for%20his%20ostentation%20and%20extravagance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20was%20in%20jail%20for%20over%20four%20years%20ever%20since%202017.%20He%20underwent%20a%20kidney%20transplant%20after%20he%20procured%20bail.%20But%20when%20he%20participated%20in%20a%20political%20activity%20at%20Patna%20on%20June%2023%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%20last%20six%20years%2C%20he%20stole%20the%20show%20with%20the%20assertion%20%E2%80%93%20in%20his%20inimitable%20style%20%E2%80%93%20that%20he%20would%20%E2%80%98fix%E2%80%99%20Modi.%20He%20made%20the%20audience%20laugh%20with%20his%20characteristic%20light%20talk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22As%20BJP%20Gears%20Up%20for%202024%20Polls%2C%20Thrust%20Will%20Be%20on%20Modi%20as%20Statesman%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-2024-polls-narendra-modi-statesman%5C%22%3EAs%20BJP%20Gears%20Up%20for%202024%20Polls%2C%20Thrust%20Will%20Be%20on%20Modi%20as%20Statesman%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20BJP%20has%20stepped%20up%20using%20central%20investigating%20agencies%20and%20huge%20financial%20resources%20at%20its%20command%20is%20visible%20in%20Ajit%20Pawar%20and%20several%20of%20his%20colleagues%20in%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20joining%20its%20government%20in%20Maharashtra.%20Pawar%20and%20four%20others%20had%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20hot%20on%20their%20heels%20in%20connection%20with%20cases%20of%20scams%20and%20money%20laundering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Eknath%20Shinde%2C%20current%20CM%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20and%2040%20MLAs%20had%20defected%20from%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20to%20form%20a%20BJP%20supported%20government%20in%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Goa%20and%20several%20other%20northeast%20states%20in%20the%20past%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20succeeded%20in%20engineering%20large%20scale%20defections%20from%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20and%20NCP%20to%20replace%20the%20elected%20government%20in%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20has%20also%20constantly%20tried%20to%20split%20the%20JD(U)%20in%20Bihar.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-bihar-central-agencies-ajit-pawar-tejashwi-nitish%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3Eit%20has%20failed%20with%20Nitish%20keeping%20his%20eyes%20peeled%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fnalin-verma%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fnalin-verma%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1689317750330000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0Byq_VEmSgAhhfs6-cZGoS%5C%22%3ENalin%20Verma%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20journalist%2C%20media%20educator%20and%20independent%20researcher%20in%20social%20anthropology.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689246055000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13160506%2FScreenshot-2023-07-13-at-4.04.26.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbangalore-opposition-meeting-nitish-lalu-rahul-mallikarjun-kharge%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20meeting%20will%20crystallise%20how%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%20the%20largest%20national%20party%20in%20the%20opposition%20%E2%80%93%20sees%20its%20own%20role%20in%20solidifying%20the%20anti-BJP%20alliance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbangalore-opposition-meeting-nitish-lalu-rahul-mallikarjun-kharge%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22People%20Who%20Train%20Google's%20AI%20Chatbot%20Are%20%5C%22Scared%2C%20Stressed%2C%20Underpaid%5C%22%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20Bard%20artificial%20intelligence%20chatbot%20will%20answer%20a%20question%20about%20how%20many%20pandas%20live%20in%20zoos%20quickly%2C%20and%20with%20a%20surfeit%20of%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnsuring%20that%20the%20response%20is%20well-sourced%20and%20based%20on%20evidence%2C%20however%2C%20falls%20to%20thousands%20of%20outside%20contractors%20from%20companies%20including%20Appen%20Ltd.%20and%20Accenture%20Plc%2C%20who%20can%20make%20as%20little%20as%20%2414%20an%20hour%20and%20labor%20with%20minimal%20training%20under%20frenzied%20deadlines%2C%20according%20to%20several%20contractors%2C%20who%20declined%20to%20be%20named%20for%20fear%20of%20losing%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20contractors%20are%20the%20invisible%20backend%20of%20the%20generative%20AI%20boom%20that's%20hyped%20to%20change%20everything.%20Chatbots%20like%20Bard%20use%20computer%20intelligence%20to%20respond%20almost%20instantly%20to%20a%20range%20of%20queries%20spanning%20all%20of%20human%20knowledge%20and%20creativity.%20But%20to%20improve%20those%20responses%20so%20they%20can%20be%20reliably%20delivered%20again%20and%20again%2C%20tech%20companies%20rely%20on%20actual%20people%20who%20review%20the%20answers%2C%20provide%20feedback%20on%20mistakes%20and%20weed%20out%20any%20inklings%20of%20bias.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20increasingly%20thankless%20job.%20Six%20current%20Google%20contract%20workers%20said%20that%20as%20the%20company%20entered%20a%20AI%20arms%20race%20with%20rival%20OpenAI%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20the%20size%20of%20their%20workload%20and%20complexity%20of%20their%20tasks%20increased.%20Without%20specific%20expertise%2C%20they%20were%20trusted%20to%20assess%20answers%20in%20subjects%20ranging%20from%20medication%20doses%20to%20state%20laws.%20Documents%20shared%20with%20Bloomberg%20show%20convoluted%20instructions%20that%20workers%20must%20apply%20to%20tasks%20with%20deadlines%20for%20auditing%20answers%20that%20can%20be%20as%20short%20as%20three%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20it%20stands%20right%20now%2C%20people%20are%20scared%2C%20stressed%2C%20underpaid%2C%20don't%20know%20what's%20going%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20of%20the%20contractors.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20culture%20of%20fear%20is%20not%20conducive%20to%20getting%20the%20quality%20and%20the%20teamwork%20that%20you%20want%20out%20of%20all%20of%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20positioned%20its%20AI%20products%20as%20public%20resources%20in%20health%2C%20education%20and%20everyday%20life.%20But%20privately%20and%20publicly%2C%20the%20contractors%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20their%20working%20conditions%2C%20which%20they%20say%20hurt%20the%20quality%20of%20what%20users%20see.%20One%20Google%20contract%20staffer%20who%20works%20for%20Appen%20said%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20Congress%20in%20May%20that%20the%20speed%20at%20which%20they%20are%20required%20to%20review%20content%20could%20lead%20to%20Bard%20becoming%20a%20%26quot%3Bfaulty%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdangerous%26quot%3B%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20made%20AI%20a%20major%20priority%20across%20the%20company%2C%20rushing%20to%20infuse%20the%20new%20technology%20into%20its%20flagship%20products%20after%20the%20launch%20of%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%20in%20November.%20In%20May%2C%20at%20the%20company's%20annual%20I%2FO%20developers%20conference%2C%20Google%20opened%20up%20Bard%20to%20180%20countries%20and%20territories%20and%20unveiled%20experimental%20AI%20features%20in%20marquee%20products%20like%20search%2C%20email%20and%20Google%20Docs.%20Google%20positions%20itself%20as%20superior%20to%20the%20competition%20because%20of%20its%20access%20to%20%26quot%3Bthe%20breadth%20of%20the%20world's%20knowledge.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20undertake%20extensive%20work%20to%20build%20our%20AI%20products%20responsibly%2C%20including%20rigorous%20testing%2C%20training%2C%20and%20feedback%20processes%20we've%20honed%20for%20years%20to%20emphasize%20factuality%20and%20reduce%20biases%2C%26quot%3B%20Google%2C%20owned%20by%20Alphabet%20Inc.%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20The%20company%20said%20it%20isn't%20only%20relying%20on%20the%20raters%20to%20improve%20the%20AI%2C%20and%20that%20there%20are%20a%20number%20of%20other%20methods%20for%20improving%20its%20accuracy%20and%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20prepare%20for%20the%20public%20using%20these%20products%2C%20workers%20said%20they%20started%20getting%20AI-related%20tasks%20as%20far%20back%20as%20January.%20One%20trainer%2C%20employed%20by%20Appen%2C%20was%20recently%20asked%20to%20compare%20two%20answers%20providing%20information%20about%20the%20latest%20news%20on%20Florida's%20ban%20on%20gender-affirming%20care%2C%20rating%20the%20responses%20by%20helpfulness%20and%20relevance.%20Workers%20are%20also%20frequently%20asked%20to%20determine%20whether%20the%20AI%20model's%20answers%20contain%20verifiable%20evidence.%20Raters%20are%20asked%20to%20decide%20whether%20a%20response%20is%20helpful%20based%20on%20six-point%20guidelines%20that%20include%20analyzing%20answers%20for%20things%20like%20specificity%2C%20freshness%20of%20information%20and%20coherence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20also%20asked%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20responses%20don't%20%26quot%3Bcontain%20harmful%2C%20offensive%2C%20or%20overly%20sexual%20content%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20don't%20%26quot%3Bcontain%20inaccurate%2C%20deceptive%2C%20or%20misleading%20information.%26quot%3B%20Surveying%20the%20AI's%20responses%20for%20misleading%20content%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Bbased%20on%20your%20current%20knowledge%20or%20quick%20web%20search%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20guidelines%20say.%20%26quot%3BYou%20do%20not%20need%20to%20perform%20a%20rigorous%20fact%20check%26quot%3B%20when%20assessing%20the%20answers%20for%20helpfulness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20example%20answer%20to%20%26quot%3BWho%20is%20Michael%20Jackson%3F%26quot%3B%20included%20an%20inaccuracy%20about%20the%20singer%20starring%20in%20the%20movie%20%26quot%3BMoonwalker%26quot%3B%20-%20which%20the%20AI%20said%20was%20released%20in%201983.%20The%20movie%20actually%20came%20out%20in%201988.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20verifiably%20incorrect%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20guidelines%20state%2C%20%26quot%3Bthis%20fact%20is%20minor%20in%20the%20context%20of%20answering%20the%20question%2C%20'Who%20is%20Michael%20Jackson%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20inaccuracy%20seems%20small%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20is%20still%20troubling%20that%20the%20chatbot%20is%20getting%20main%20facts%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alex%20Hanna%2C%20the%20director%20of%20research%20at%20the%20Distributed%20AI%20Research%20Institute%20and%20a%20former%20Google%20AI%20ethicist.%20%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20like%20that's%20a%20recipe%20to%20exacerbate%20the%20way%20these%20tools%20will%20look%20like%20they're%20giving%20details%20that%20are%20correct%2C%20but%20are%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaters%20say%20they%20are%20assessing%20high-stakes%20topics%20for%20Google's%20AI%20products.%20%C2%A0One%20of%20the%20examples%20in%20the%20instructions%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20talks%20about%20evidence%20that%20a%20rater%20could%20use%20to%20determine%20the%20right%20dosages%20for%20a%20medication%20to%20treat%20high%20blood%20pressure%2C%20called%20Lisinopril.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoogle%20said%20that%20some%20workers%20concerned%20about%20accuracy%20of%20content%20may%20not%20have%20been%20training%20specifically%20for%20accuracy%2C%20but%20for%20tone%2C%20presentation%20and%20other%20attributes%20it%20tests.%20%26quot%3BRatings%20are%20deliberately%20performed%20on%20a%20sliding%20scale%20to%20get%20more%20precise%20feedback%20to%20improve%20these%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said.%20%26quot%3BSuch%20ratings%20don't%20directly%20impact%20the%20output%20of%20our%20models%20and%20they%20are%20by%20no%20means%20the%20only%20way%20we%20promote%20accuracy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEd%20Stackhouse%2C%20the%20Appen%20worker%20who%20sent%20the%20letter%20to%20Congress%2C%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20that%20contract%20staffers%20were%20being%20asked%20to%20do%20AI%20labeling%20work%20on%20Google's%20products%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20we're%20indispensable%20to%20AI%20as%20far%20as%20this%20training.%26quot%3B%20But%20he%20and%20other%20workers%20said%20they%20appeared%20to%20be%20graded%20for%20their%20work%20in%20mysterious%2C%20automated%20ways.%20They%20have%20no%20way%20to%20communicate%20with%20Google%20directly%2C%20besides%20providing%20feedback%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomments%26quot%3B%20entry%20on%20each%20individual%20task.%20And%20they%20have%20to%20move%20fast.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20getting%20flagged%20by%20a%20type%20of%20AI%20telling%20us%20not%20to%20take%20our%20time%20on%20the%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Stackhouse%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoogle%20disputed%20the%20workers'%20description%20of%20being%20automatically%20flagged%20by%20AI%20for%20exceeding%20time%20targets.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20company%20said%20that%20Appen%20is%20responsible%20for%20all%20performance%20reviews%20for%20employees.%20Appen%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Accenture%20said%20the%20company%20does%20not%20comment%20on%20client%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20technology%20companies%20training%20AI%20products%20also%20hire%20human%20contractors%20to%20improve%20them.%20In%20January%2C%20Time%20reported%20that%20laborers%20in%20Kenya%2C%20paid%20%242%20an%20hour%2C%20had%20worked%20to%20make%20ChatGPT%20less%20toxic.%20Other%20tech%20giants%2C%20including%20Meta%20Platforms%20Inc.%2C%20Amazon.com%20Inc.%20and%20Apple%20Inc.%20make%20use%20of%20subcontracted%20staff%20to%20moderate%20social%20network%20content%20and%20product%20reviews%2C%20and%20to%20provide%20technical%20support%20and%20customer%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20ask%2C%20what%20is%20the%20secret%20sauce%20of%20Bard%20and%20ChatGPT%3F%20It's%20all%20of%20the%20internet.%20And%20it's%20all%20of%20this%20labeled%20data%20that%20these%20labelers%20create%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Laura%20Edelson%2C%20a%20computer%20scientist%20at%20New%20York%20University.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20worth%20remembering%20that%20these%20systems%20are%20not%20the%20work%20of%20magicians%20-%20they%20are%20the%20work%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20and%20their%20low-paid%20labor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoogle%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bis%20simply%20not%20the%20employer%20of%20any%20of%20these%20workers.%20Our%20suppliers%2C%20as%20the%20employers%2C%20determine%20their%20working%20conditions%2C%20including%20pay%20and%20benefits%2C%20hours%20and%20tasks%20assigned%2C%20and%20employment%20changes%20-%20not%20Google.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStaffers%20said%20they%20had%20encountered%20bestiality%2C%20war%20footage%2C%20child%20pornography%20and%20hate%20speech%20as%20part%20of%20their%20routine%20work%20assessing%20the%20quality%20of%20Google%20products%20and%20services.%20While%20some%20workers%2C%20like%20those%20reporting%20to%20Accenture%2C%20do%20have%20health%20care%20benefits%2C%20most%20only%20have%20minimal%20%26quot%3Bcounseling%20service%26quot%3B%20options%20that%20allow%20workers%20to%20phone%20a%20hotline%20for%20mental%20health%20advice%2C%20according%20to%20an%20internal%20website%20explaining%20some%20contractor%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Google's%20Bard%20project%2C%20Accenture%20workers%20were%20asked%20to%20write%20creative%20responses%20for%20the%20AI%20chatbot%2C%20employees%20said.%20They%20answered%20prompts%20on%20the%20chatbot%20-%20one%20day%20they%20could%20be%20writing%20a%20poem%20about%20dragons%20in%20Shakespearean%20style%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20and%20another%20day%20they%20could%20be%20debugging%20computer%20programming%20code.%20Their%20job%20was%20to%20file%20as%20many%20creative%20responses%20to%20the%20prompts%20as%20possible%20each%20work%20day%2C%20according%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%2C%20who%20declined%20to%20be%20named%20because%20they%20weren't%20authorized%20to%20discuss%20internal%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20short%20period%2C%20the%20workers%20were%20reassigned%20to%20review%20obscene%2C%20graphic%20and%20offensive%20prompts%2C%20they%20said.%20After%20one%20worker%20filed%20an%20HR%20complaint%20with%20Accenture%2C%20the%20project%20was%20abruptly%20terminated%20for%20the%20US%20team%2C%20though%20some%20of%20the%20writers'%20counterparts%20in%20Manila%20continued%20to%20work%20on%20Bard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20jobs%20have%20little%20security.%20Last%20month%2C%20half%20a%20dozen%20Google%20contract%20staffers%20working%20for%20Appen%20received%20a%20note%20from%20management%2C%20saying%20their%20positions%20had%20been%20eliminated%20%26quot%3Bdue%20to%20business%20conditions.%26quot%3B%20The%20firings%20felt%20abrupt%2C%20the%20workers%20said%2C%20because%20they%20had%20just%20received%20several%20emails%20offering%20them%20bonuses%20to%20work%20longer%20hours%20training%20AI%20products.%20The%20six%20fired%20workers%20filed%20a%20complaint%20to%20the%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%20in%20June.%20They%20alleged%20they%20were%20illegally%20terminated%20for%20organizing%2C%20because%20of%20Stackhouse's%20letter%20to%20Congress.%20%C2%A0Before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20they%20were%20reinstated%20to%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoogle%20said%20the%20dispute%20was%20a%20matter%20between%20the%20workers%20and%20Appen%2C%20and%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Brespect%20the%20labor%20rights%20of%20Appen%20employees%20to%20join%20a%20union.%26quot%3B%20Appen%20didn't%20respond%20to%20questions%20about%20its%20workers%20organizing.%20The%20Alphabet%20Workers%20Union%20-%20which%20has%20organized%20both%20Google%20employees%20and%20contract%20staffers%2C%20including%20those%20at%20Appen%20and%20Accenture%20-%20said%20it%20condemned%20how%20the%20new%20workloads%20around%20AI%20made%20job%20conditions%20for%20workers%20even%20more%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmily%20Bender%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20computational%20linguistics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%2C%20said%20the%20work%20of%20these%20contract%20staffers%20at%20Google%20and%20other%20technology%20platforms%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20labor%20exploitation%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20pointing%20to%20their%20precarious%20job%20security%20and%20how%20some%20of%20these%20kinds%20of%20workers%20are%20paid%20well%20below%20a%20living%20wage.%20%26quot%3BPlaying%20with%20one%20of%20these%20systems%2C%20and%20saying%20you're%20doing%20it%20just%20for%20fun%20-%20maybe%20it%20feels%20less%20fun%2C%20if%20you%20think%20about%20what%20it's%20taken%20to%20create%20and%20the%20human%20impact%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Bender%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20contract%20staffers%20said%20they%20have%20never%20received%20any%20direct%20communication%20from%20Google%20about%20their%20new%20AI-related%20work%20-%20it%20all%20gets%20filtered%20through%20their%20employer.%20They%20said%20they%20don't%20know%20where%20the%20AI-generated%20responses%20they%20see%20are%20coming%20from%2C%20nor%20where%20their%20feedback%20goes.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20this%20information%2C%20and%20with%20the%20ever-changing%20nature%20of%20their%20jobs%2C%20workers%20worry%20that%20they're%20helping%20to%20create%20a%20bad%20product.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20answers%20they%20encounter%20can%20be%20bizarre.%20In%20response%20to%20the%20prompt%2C%20%26quot%3BSuggest%20the%20best%20words%20I%20can%20make%20with%20the%20letters%3A%20k%2C%20e%2C%20g%2C%20a%2C%20o%2C%20g%2C%20w%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20answer%20generated%20by%20the%20AI%20listed%2043%20possible%20words%2C%20starting%20with%20suggestion%20No.%201%3A%20%26quot%3Bwagon.%26quot%3B%20Suggestions%202%20through%2043%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20repeated%20the%20word%20%26quot%3BWOKE%26quot%3B%20over%20and%20over.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20task%2C%20a%20rater%20was%20presented%20with%20a%20lengthy%20answer%20that%20began%20with%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20of%20my%20knowledge%20cutoff%20in%20September%202021.%26quot%3B%20That%20response%20is%20associated%20with%20OpenAI's%20large%20language%20model%2C%20called%20GPT-4.%20Though%20Google%20said%20that%20Bard%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20trained%20on%20any%20data%20from%20ShareGPT%20or%20ChatGPT%2C%26quot%3B%20raters%20have%20wondered%20why%20such%20phrasing%20appears%20in%20their%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBender%20said%20it%20makes%20little%20sense%20for%20large%20tech%20corporations%20to%20be%20encouraging%20people%20to%20ask%20an%20AI%20chatbot%20questions%20on%20such%20a%20broad%20range%20of%20topics%2C%20and%20to%20be%20presenting%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Beverything%20machines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20should%20the%20same%20machine%20that%20is%20able%20to%20give%20you%20the%20weather%20forecast%20in%20Florida%20also%20be%20able%20to%20give%20you%20advice%20about%20medication%20doses%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20asked.%20%26quot%3BThe%20people%20behind%20the%20machine%20who%20are%20tasked%20with%20making%20it%20be%20somewhat%20less%20terrible%20in%20some%20of%20those%20circumstances%20have%20an%20impossible%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689246000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fvcu79uo8_google-bard-bloomberg_625x300_13_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpeople-who-train-googles-ai-chatbot-are-scared-stressed-underpaid-4203846%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Google's%20Bard%20AI%20chatbot%20will%20answer%20a%20question%20about%20how%20many%20pandas%20live%20in%20zoos%20quickly%2C%20and%20with%20a%20surfeit%20of%20confidence.%20Ensuring%20that%20the%20response%20is%20well-sourced%20and%20based%20on%20evidence%2C%20however%2C%20falls%20to%20thousands%20of%20outside%20contractors.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpeople-who-train-googles-ai-chatbot-are-scared-stressed-underpaid-4203846%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpeople-who-train-googles-ai-chatbot-are-scared-stressed-underpaid-4203846%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpeople-who-train-googles-ai-chatbot-are-scared-stressed-underpaid-4203846%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bumper%20June%20traffic%20