%20supply%20chain%20for%20these%20women%3F%E2%80%99%20and%20then%20in%20September%202021%2C%20Aazol%20was%20born%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faazol-5-1688737718.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22women%20from%20remote%20village%20in%20Maharashtra%20working%20for%20Aazol%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faazol-5-1688737718.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faazol-5-1688737718-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faazol-5-1688737718-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faazol-5-1688737718-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Faazol-5-1688737718-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-323132%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EApurva%20left%20her%20three%20decades%20of%20corporate%20career%20to%20work%20in%20the%20social%20sector%3B%20Picture%20credit%3A%20Apurva%20Purohit%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMaking%20rare%20foods%20available%20to%20the%20world%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mother-son%20team%20went%20to%20various%20remote%20villages%20in%20search%20of%20authentic%20food%20made%20by%20the%20locals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20son%20even%20visited%20Naxalite%20villages%20to%20get%20their%20authentic%20snacks%20and%20bring%20them%20to%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20the%20tribal%20women%20in%20some%20villages%20make%20mahua%3Cem%3E%20ladoos%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20are%20made%20using%20mahua%20flower